File: A factory worker. AFP/STR JOHANNESBURG - Evidence of the severe impact of power cuts on the economy continues to emerge in industry reports and surveys. ABSA’s Purchasing Managers Index fell sharply in February. READ: Eskom preparing schedules beyond Stage 8 At 48.8 points, the Index fell below the neutral 50-point mark, pointing to a marked deterioration in business conditions in the factory sector. Manufacturing is SA’s fourth-largest industry, contributing 14 percent to GDP. Researchers say the period included an unprecedented seven consecutive days of Stage 6 power cuts, which was likely top of mind for many respondents.